{
  "texts": [
    "We designed three groups of six vignettes in which protagonists expressed either sadness, anger, or anxiety.",
    "Each vignette included a brief situation and a description of how it made the protagonist of the vignette feel, without directly specifying the emotion (e.g., \"My friend forgot my birthday after saying we'd go to dinner together.",
    "I feel unwanted.\").",
    "We specifically aimed to make sure that all vignettes are as similar as possible to make sure that variance in reappraisal is driven mostly by reappraisal style rather than the specific scenario that they were addressing.",
    "Generating human reappraisals."
  ]
}